" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"Φηλικίων\">Φηλικίων\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"χρηστὲ\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"χρηστός\">χρηστὲ\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"καὶ\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"καί\">καὶ\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"ἄμεμπτε\" data-n=\"50\" data-lemma=\"ἄμεμπτος\">ἄμεμπτε\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"χαῖρε\" data-n=\"60\" data-lemma=\"χαίρω\">χαῖρε\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"Γαι\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Γαίους\">Γ\u003C/span>·\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ματρίνι\">\u003Cspan data-text=\"Ματρίνι\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"Ματρίνιος\">ΜΑΤΡΙΝΙ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Φηλικίων\">\u003Cspan data-text=\"Φηλικίων\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"Φηλικίων\">ΦΗΛΙΚΙΩΝ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>·\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"χρηστὲ\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"χρηστός\">ΧΡΗ\u003C/span>·\u003Cspan data-text=\"καὶ\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"καί\">ΚΑΙ\u003C/span>·\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἄμεμπτε\" data-n=\"50\" data-lemma=\"ἄμεμπτος\">ΑΜΕ\u003C/span>·\u003Cspan data-text=\"χαῖρε\" data-n=\"60\" data-lemma=\"χαίρω\">ΧΑΙΡΕ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Victoria Fendel, Robert Crellin\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic-simple-lemmatized\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan data-text=\"Γαι\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Γαίους\">ΓΑΙ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"Ματρίνι\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"Ματρίνιος\">ΜΑΤΡΙΝΙ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"Φηλικίων\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"Φηλικίων\">ΦΗΛΙΚΙΩΝ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"χρηστὲ\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"χρηστός\">ΧΡΗΣΤΕ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"καὶ\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"καί\">ΚΑΙ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἄμεμπτε\" data-n=\"50\" data-lemma=\"ἄμεμπτος\">ΑΜΕΜΠΤΕ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"χαῖρε\" data-n=\"60\" data-lemma=\"χαίρω\">ΧΑΙΡΕ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003359_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag, Aut. Assessorato Beni Culturali Regione Siciliana n.10681 del 06/05/2014\" src=\"ISic003359_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003359.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag, Aut. Assessorato Beni Culturali Regione Siciliana n.10681 del 06/05/2014\" src=\"ISic003359-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003359_threequarter_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag, Aut. Assessorato Beni Culturali Regione Siciliana n.10681 del 06/05/2014\" src=\"ISic003359_threequarter_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003359_threequarter.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag, Aut. Assessorato Beni Culturali Regione Siciliana n.10681 del 06/05/2014\" src=\"ISic003359_threequarter-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>  \u003Cspan>Text from autopsy\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Gaius Matrinius Felicio, worthy and blameless, farewell!\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Φηλικίων presumably renders the Latin Felicio. Although the inscription is in Greek, it is noteworthy that it employs a Latin vocative form for Matrinius (implicit therefore also for Gaius), as well as abbreviating the formulaic words χρηστὲ and ἄμεμπτε, according to the more normal practices of Latin inscriptions; the use of interpuncts throughout is also distinctively Latin in practice. Ferrua suggests that the letters are of the end of the third century AD, but an earlier date also seems possible, and indeed likely.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Ferrua 1941 217 no.97 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001456\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001456\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\"> \u003Cp>Somewhat irregular sized letters, not strictly following the horizontal. Pronounced but simple heavy serifs on deep v-cut letters. Alpha has extended top stroke, with cross-bar sloping down to the left; epsilon is lunate; kappa has short equal length arms; mu has four equal slopint strokes; rho has a large just closed eye; phi has ovoid body with standard height vertical; omega is cursive.\u003C/p> Lines 1-3  35-60  Interlineation line 1 to 2  not measured  \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[202,205,208,211,214,217,220,223],{"id":203,"html":204},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"Γαι\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Γαίους\">Γ(αι)\u003C/span> 